NOTE:PROFESSIONAL PROFILE\n\nCurrent Role: CEO of Cobra Group\, which operates through Cobra Projects\, Cobra Fire\, and Cobra Tech.\n\nCompany Background: Cobra Projects was founded in Johannesburg in 1986. The company designs and manufactures customised mining support vehicles and firefighting equipment for open-cast and underground mining environments across Africa and internationally. Product range includes articulated fuel and lube trucks\, diesel bowsers\, water carts\, stemming trucks\, mine firefighting trucks\, and off-road low-bed trailers.\n\nNotable Achievements: Under Darby's leadership\, Cobra developed what is believed to be a world-first: an all-terrain vehicle combining a rescue and firefighting aerial sky-lift platform with a 21\,000-litre tank incorporating an aqueous firefighting foam compartment. Also developed stemming truck technology enabling one operator to stem 300 holes per shift.\n\nAlterra Capital Partners acquired a stake in Cobra Group Holdings.\n\nSources:\nhttps://www.cobraprojects.com/\nhttps://www.cobraprojects.com/contact-us\nhttps://www.africaprivateequitynews.com/p/alterra-capital-takes-stake-in-johannesburg\nhttps://www.emergencyvehicleresponse.com/new-type-of-fire-apparatus-in-south-africa/
